eText\":\"OK\",\"result\":\"# Runner Context Documentation\\n\\nThe `runner` context provides information about the runner executing the current job. Here's the complete reference:\\n\\n## Property Table\\n\\n| Property name        | Type     | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             |\\n| -------------------- | -------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\\n| `runner`             | `object` | This context changes for each job in a workflow run. This object contains all the properties listed below.                                                                                                                                                              |\\n| `runner.name`        | `string` | The name of the runner executing the job. This name may not be unique in a workflow run as runners at the repository and organization levels could use the same name.                                                                                                   |\\n| `runner.os`          | `string` | The operating system of the runner executing the job. Possible values are `Linux`, `Windows`, or `macOS`.                                                                                                                                                               |\\n| `runner.arch`        | `string` | The architecture of the runner executing the job. Possible values are `X86`, `X64`, `ARM`, or `ARM64`.                                                                                                                                                                  |\\n| `runner.temp`        | `string` | \\\"The path to a temporary directory on the runner. This directory is emptied at the beginning and end of each job.\\\"                                                                                                                                                      |\\n| `runner.tool_cache`  | `string` | The path to the directory containing preinstalled tools for GitHub-hosted runners. For more information, see [GitHub-hosted runners](/en/actions/using-github-hosted-runners/about-github-hosted-runners#supported-software).                                           |\\n| `runner.debug`       | `string` | This is set only if [debug logging](/en/actions/monitoring-and-troubleshooting-workflows/enabling-debug-logging) is enabled, and always has the value of `1`. It can be useful as an indicator to enable additional debugging or verbose logging in your own job steps. |\\n| `runner.environment` | `string` | The environment of the runner executing the job. Possible values are: `github-hosted` for GitHub-hosted runners provided by GitHub, and `self-hosted` for self-hosted runners configured by the repository owner.                                                       |\\n\\n## Key Note on `runner.temp`\\n\\nThe temporary directory property provides workspace for storing files during job execution. \\\"Note that files will not be removed if the runner's user account does not have permission to delete them.\\\"\",\"durationMs\":7392,\"url\":\"https://docs.github.com/en/actions/writing-workflows/choosing-what-your-workflow-does/accessing-contextual-information-about-workflow-runs#runner-context\"},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"ad7afc2c-f49c-4496-8ad6-59d8f218dfa7\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"8497bc6b-f157-45b0-b80e-80e68d079de6\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"9cab4869-39ad-42e6-8216-8140fd54db35\",\"version\":\"2.1.69\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/fix-releaser\",\"slug\":\"kind-bubbling-nova\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01RZihfWGgaKUvzhtsrneEb7\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Here's the deal:\\n\\n**`runner.temp`** is a **context property** — used in GitHub Actions expressions with `${{ }}` syntax:\\n```yaml\\nargs: release --clean --release-notes=${{ runner.temp }}/release_notes.md\\n```\\n\\n**`RUNNER_TEMP`** is the corresponding **environment variable** — automatically set by GitHub Actions, used in shell `run:` blocks:\\n```yaml\\nrun: |\\n  echo \\\"$RUNNER_TEMP\\\"  # same path as runner.temp\\n```\\n\\nThey point to the same directory. The difference is just where you use them:\\n- **Shell code** (`run:` blocks) → `$RUNNER_TEMP`\\n- **YAML expressions** (`with:`, `if:`, etc.) → `${{ runner.temp }}`\\n\\nThe `with:` block for GoReleaser isn't a shell script — it's YAML input to the action, so it needs the `${{ runner.temp }}` expression syntax. The `run:` block is a shell script, so it uses `$RUNNER_TEMP`.\\n\\nPer the docs: it's a temp directory on the runner that gets **emptied at the beginning and end of each job**, so it's perfect for intermediate files like release notes.\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":716,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":26493,\"output_tokens\":289,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":716,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYn4zbkyjPEM5eXTRrqvX\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"39ea7d3e-f2dc-4fd2-b233-dc7cd129d1c9\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T15:33:25.046Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"39ea7d3e-f2dc-4fd2-b233-dc7cd129d1c9\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cl